u0435\\u0445\\u0430\\u043d\\u0438\\u043a\\u0438\\\", \\u0433.\\u0412\\u00a0\\u0423\\u0444\\u0430, \\u0420\\u043e\\u0441\\u0441\\u0438\\u044f<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=1615\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=178&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=178&output=pdf&option_lang=rus\"},{\"title\":\"HTML \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=178&output=htm&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=178&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[\"517.958\"]', ' В работе рассмотрена одна подмодель движения газа с линейным полем скоростей. Ее образует система нелинейных дифференциальных уравнений большого порядка с начальными данными. Найдено несколько первых интегралов такой системы. В результате чего порядок системы снижен. Для специальных начальных данных задачи найдено приближенное решение дифференциальных уравнений подмодели. Такому решению соответствуют мировые линии, описывающие радиальный разлет частиц газа из вихря. Построены траектории движения частиц газа. ', 'газовая динамика, подмодель, приближенное решение, радиальный разлет.', '', '[\"178_147.pdf\"]', '[\"178_650.pdf\",\"178_817.html\"]', '13.01.2012'),
(178, 179, 'Local and nonlocal conserved vectors for the nonlinear filtration equation', '[{\"title\":\"A. A. Alexandrova\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=78141\"},{\"title\":\"N. Rani Rani bragimov\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=22634\"},{\"title\":\"K. V. Imamutdinova\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=78142\"},{\"title\":\"V. O. Lukashchuk\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=51946\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"<i>Laboratory Group analysis of mathematical models in natural and engineering sciences, Ufa State Aviation Technical University, Ufa, Russia<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=1360\"},{\"title\":\"<i>Research Centre ALGA: Advances in Lie Group Analysis, Blekinge Institute of Technology, Karlskrona, Sweden<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=6415\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=179&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=179&output=pdf&option_lang=rus\"},{\"title\":\"HTML \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=179&output=htm&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=179&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[\"517.958\"]', ' It is demonstrated that the nonlinear filtration equation is nonlinarly selfadjoint. Using this property, the conserved vectors associated with Lie point and nonlocal symmetries are constructed. ', 'nonlinear filtration equation, nonlinear self-adjointness, Lie point and nonlocal symmetries, conserved vectors.', '', '[\"179_920.pdf\"]', '[\"179_138.pdf\",\"179_655.html\"]', '29.10.2012'),
(179, 180, 'The non-autonomous dynamical systems and exact solutions with superposition principle for evolutionary PDEs', '[{\"title\":\"V. A. Dorodnitsyn\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=37013\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"<i>Keldysh Institute of Applied Mathematics RAS, Moscow, Russia<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=843\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=180&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=180&output=pdf&option_lang=rus\"},{\"title\":\"HTML \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=180&output=htm&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=180&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[]', ' In the present article we introduce a new application of S. Lie\'s non-autonomous dynamical systems with the generalized separation of variables in right hand-sides. We consider non-autonomous dynamical equations as some sort of external action on a given evolution equation, which transforms a subset of solutions into itself. The goal of our approach is to find a subset of solutions of an evolution equation with a superposition principle. This leads to an integration of ordinary differential equations in a process of constructing exact solutions of PDEs. In this paper we consider the application of the most simple one-dimensional case of the Lie theorem. ', 'evolutionary equations, exact solutions, superposition of solutions.', '', '[\"180_292.pdf\"]', '[\"180_874.pdf\",\"180_545.html\"]', '27.10.2012');
