(180, 181, 'On infinitesimal reciprocal-type transformations in gasdynamics. Lie group connections and nonlinear self-adjointness', '[{\"title\":\"N. Rani Rani bragimov\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=22634\"},{\"title\":\"C. Rogers\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/person.phtml?option_lang=rus&personid=19157\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"<i>Laboratory Group analysis of mathematical models in natural and engineering sciences, Ufa State Aviation Technical University, Ufa, Russia<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=1360\"},{\"title\":\"<i>Research Centre ALGA: Advances in Lie Group Analysis, Blekinge Institute of Technology, Karlskrona, Sweden<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=6415\"},{\"title\":\"<i>Clare Hall, University of Cambridge, UK<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=1411\"},{\"title\":\"<i>Australian Research Council Centre of Excellence for Mathematics and Statistics of Complex Systems, School of Mathematics and Statistics, University of New South Wales, Sydney, Australia<\\/i>\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/organisation.phtml?option_lang=rus&orgid=4296\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=181&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=181&output=pdf&option_lang=rus\"},{\"title\":\"HTML \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getRefFromDB.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=181&output=htm&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"PDF \\u0444\\u0430\\u0439\\u043b\",\"href\":\"\\/php\\/getFT.phtml?jrnid=ufa&paperid=181&what=fullt&option_lang=rus\"}]', '[\"517.958\"]', ' Bateman-type reciprocal transformations are represented as non-local infinitesimal symmetries of the governing equations of steady, two-dimensional, inviscid gasdynamics. In particular, this representation allows the construction of a novel non-local conservation law using the recently introduced concept of nonlinear self-adjointness. ', 'Bateman-type reciprocal transformations, gasdynamics, non-local symmetries and conservation laws.', '', '[\"181_935.pdf\"]', '[\"181_403.pdf\",\"181_392.html\"]', '09.11.2012'),
